      "message": "I think the HAVE_WIFI is pretty much going be in sansa connect config and wrapping this here with #ifndef HAVE_WIFI just doesn\u0027t seem justified to me.\n\nI don\u0027t think this code belongs here at all though - I originally put it here because I didn\u0027t have any better place for it. Also, the importance of this is much smaller than the importance of PD (configured via AVR command). Basically setting PD to 0 equals really significant current reduction (as compared to PD equal 1), while setting CS and reset change close to nothing if PD is 0 (which is default after booting).",
